author: COMSOL
description: This transient model uses the Two-Phase Flow, Level Set, Laminar Flow interface to model the impact of a water wave on a column. A body of water with a height of 0.3Â meters is initially contained behind a gate. At the start of the simulation, the gate is suddenly released and the body of water forms a wave moving toward the structure. After impacting on the structure, the water continues until it is reflected at the wall of the tank and impinges a second time on the column. The pressure force on the column is calculated and can be compared with experimental results.
